We connect them, over the phone, for advice on their business challenges. Customers also can access to the range of courses that experts oered as part of the Social Me learning experience. Our Mission is to make Social Media and Digital Marketing advisors available every time and everywhere for entrepreneurs, professionals and business managers who want to empower themselves with the best digital skills to improve their competitiveness in the labor market.

Problem
1- Time is a scarce commodity. We nd it hard to concentrate. We live stressed by the amount of information we have to process.
2- The speed of change threatens our competitiveness and requires us to inform and to form steadily.
3- New digital Professions arise every day for business innovation, creating a growing gap between what we know and what we need to know to remain competitive.
4- We do not know where to nd quality experts to help us understand the new paradigms of the digital economy. The University can not follow the speed with which the changes occur.

Value proposition
Social Me oer a monthly-based advisory services including access to the advisors network, online courses and workshops, real-time consultation, upgrade talks and tips, in a social an collaborative environment. Our business is based on providing people the opportunity to develop their digital inuence, and thus can competitively bind to the new digital economy way. Without this knowledge, the competitiveness of their companies is compromised allowing new competitors to gain market share in the new economy, digital, and with millions of new consumers who live hyper connected and expressing new commercial consumption habits. In a world where every time we have less time and less able to concentrate, we connects professionals and entrepreneurs with top advisors & industry experts through a marketplace of most Latin- Americans world class experts ever.

Bussiness Model
Social Me generates revenue by charging:
Twenty percent in commissions of calls to experts.
Fifty dollars in each training program that each expert oers to customers. (video training).
400 dollars for each each expert certication program oers to customers. (live classes that give in three months).
Free access to webinars, tips and forums.

Potential Market
The online training market is projected at $ 2.2 billion for 2016 only in Latin America according to the report introduced by Docebo this year.

Target
Professionals between 35 and 45 years working in areas of communication, marketing, and sales that feel the need to reinvent itself and regain competitiveness they have lost in this new digital economy. They are seeking to become digital generalists and gain knowledge that allows them to think of new digital business strategies and be able to relate to the new young specialists.
Millennians and empowered entrepreneurs who are naturally digital and looking to specialize in new platforms and communication technologies, social networks and digital marketing.

Diferentiation
Real time training platform that makes Social Media and Digital Marketing advisors available at any time, 24 hours a day.
We oer our customers personalized service and mentoring to help to quickly learn to solve their problems and increase sales with new digital communication tools.
Experience unique and emotional learning. Easy, fast, anytime, anywhere.
Communities of practice and collaboration with professionals from over 15 countries.

Achievements

Over 50,000 users tested our courses as Free.
More than 60,000 professionals talk with us on our social networks.

12.short_description: Comenta TV adds social networks to live television broadcasts, enabling the producers to access behavioral data of the audiences.

18.description:
Comenta TV is a company that adds a social layer to live Television broadcasts and events in real time.

Comenta TV tools give social producers access to a mass volume of data, enabling them to find relevant tweets in real time to analyze the behavior and integrate the social audience on air with one click.

TV drives viewers to express emotions through comments on the social web. According to Nielsen 60% of TV viewers use social networks while watching TV and 30% comment about the shows they are watching. But it’s difficult for TV stakeholders to keep track of real time interactions that surround TV shows and brands. Viewers are sharing comments in Twitter in several different ways (using mentions, diverse hashtags or natural
language), making it challenging to follow the conversation beyond Twitter hashtags. Most of the information is lost.

The technology behind Comenta.TV was developed to solve this problem.By identifying viewers interactions we can offer real time metrics and analytics for networks, producers and advertisers, to help them better understand their audience (who, where, when, what, how engaged, from which source and how willing to share a show with their friends), increase engagement with custom visualizations and open new monetization’s opportunities.

Comenta TV is giving TV networks and live events producers new tools to expand their business and give advertisers new windows to reach their BEST audience:
- Algorithm to index every comment being made in social networks about a live TV show
- First screen or on air integrations to engage the audience and increase the social reach of the show. - Real time analytics tools for TV shows and advertisers to better know their audience, and how influencers interact LIVE with their content and brands
- Social TV brand affinity analysis to help brands in media buying decisions

TV networks, advertisers and production companies are paying between u$500 one shot fees, up to u$5.000 subscription fees a month for Comenta. TV technology, either to analyze their connected audience or add interactive on air enhancements into their shows or events.


Comenta LLC is incorporated in the State of
Delaware, US, and the development team is based in Buenos Aires. The company is currently working with several networks in Argentina.
